'''AllOfUs''' was an American progressive political action committee founded on September, 2016 by Yong Jung Cho, Max Berger, [[Waleed Shahid]] and former members of the [[Bernie Sanders presidential campaign, 2016]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/democrats-vs-trump/new-liberal-pac-targets-democrats-primaries-n721311|title=New progressive PAC targets Democrats for primaries|publisher=}}</ref><ref>https://www.netrootsnation.org/profile/yong-jung-chung/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/02/25/politics/dnc-chair-vote-progressives-angry-ellison-perez/index.html|title=Progressives riled up after DNC vote|first=Gregory Krieg,|last=CNN|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/feb/19/democrats-resistance-donald-trump-we-will-replace-you|title=Liberal voters warn Democratic officials: resist Trump or be replaced|first1=Lauren|last1=Gambino|first2=Adam|last2=Gabbatt|date=19 February 2017|website=the Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/anti-trump-protests-spread-democratic-leadership-sit-schumers/story?id=43533616|title=Anti-Trump Protests Spread to Democratic Leadership With Sit-In at Schumer's DC Office|first=A. B. C.|last=News|date=15 November 2016|website=ABC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2016/11/democrats-trump-protests-tea-party-231450|title=Trump protesters plan to build ‘tea party of the left’|publisher=}}</ref><ref>https://www.cnn.com/2017/02/17/politics/liberal-group-primary-challenge-democrats/index.html</ref> The organization formed with the goal of transforming the Democratic Party.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/democrats-vs-trump/new-liberal-pac-targets-democrats-primaries-n721311 | title=New progressive PAC targets Democrats for primaries}}</ref> In November, 1, 2016, AllOfUs was folded into the [[Justice Democrats]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/justicedems/status/925751071687004161|title=Justice Democrats candidates|website=[[Twitter]]|language=en|date=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Justice Democrats Merge With AllOfUs.org|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HNfmcL3-ZHE|website=YouTube|accessdate=2 November 2017|date=1 November 2017}}</ref>. 

AllOfUs launched a [[Political Action Committee | PAC]] WeWillReplaceYou in order to pressure Democrats into not cooperating with the Republican administration.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/02/17/politics/liberal-group-primary-challenge-democrats/index.html | title=Liberal group threatens to challenge Dems with primary fights}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/1702/22/se.01.html | title=CNN.com - Transcripts}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.brookings.edu/blog/fixgov/2017/12/12/activist-groups-are-amateurizing-our-political-candidates/ | title=Activist groups are 'amateurizing' our political candidates| date=2017-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/wp/2017/05/15/progressives-launch-challenges-to-democrats-and-a-congressman-signs-up/?utm_term=.2aa68f86d7c1 | title=Progressives launch challenges to Democrats, and a congressman signs up}}</ref>

