'''Julian Gonsalves''' is an Indian environmentalist.

Gonslaves  is originally from the region of [[Goa]], in western India and he received a PhD in sustainable agriculture from the [[Cornell University]].<ref name="Vaz">J. Clement Vaz, [https://books.google.com/books?id=7DJLxYBYA-YC&pg=PA338&dq=%22Julian+Gonsalves%22&hl=en&ei=LSJFTonmCuqxsALX0ZGSCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CEoQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=%22Julian%20Gonsalves%22&f=false Profiles of eminent Goans, past and present ], Concept Publishing,  1997, {{ISBN|81-7022-619-8}}; p. 338</ref>
has served as the vice-president of the [[International Institute for Rural Reconstruction]], based in the Philippines.<ref name="Vaz"/><ref>[[United Nations Environment Programme]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=2K2ICLccSH0C&pg=PA87&dq=%22Julian+Gonsalves%22&hl=en&ei=jCJFTqTLB_CssAKWncSSCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CFQQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=%22Julian%20Gonsalves%22&f=false 1987-1992, the global 500: the roll of honour for environmental achievement],  Nairobi, 1993, {{ISBN|92-807-1361-2}}; pp. 87-88</ref>

Gonsalves is known for his work in the field of international rural and agricultural development, and is an awardee of the [[Sustainable Agriculture and Rural Development Award]] from Germany, bestowed on him in 1997.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o4FDAAAAYAAJ|title=Data India|date=1991-01-01|publisher=Press Institute of India|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=7DJLxYBYA-YC&pg=PA338&dq=%2522Julian+Gonsalves%2522++award#v=onepage&q=%2522Julian%2520Gonsalves%2522%2520%2520award&f=false|title=Profiles of Eminent Goans, Past and Present|last=Vaz|first=J. Clement|date=1997-01-01|publisher=Concept Publishing Company|isbn=9788170226192|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.global500.org/ViewLaureate.asp?ID%3D317 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-12-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622055234/http://www.global500.org/ViewLaureate.asp?ID=317 |archivedate=22 June 2011 |df= }}</ref>

He also won the [[Global 500 Roll of Honour]] award from the [[United Nations Environment Programme]] in 1991.<ref>[http://www.global500.org/ViewLaureate.asp?ID=317 Adult Award Winner in 1991] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622055234/http://www.global500.org/ViewLaureate.asp?ID=317 |date=22 June 2011 }}, Global 500 Forum,   [[United Nations Environment Programme]]. Accessed 12 August 2011</ref>
During his stint at the [[IIRR]], he has been heading its appropriate technology unit and was also later the [[IIRR]]'s vice president for programs.

Gonsalves has proposed, field-tested, and developed the participatory workshop process for documenting best practices, now considered one of the more innovative services provided by [[IIRR]].

He has also worked as a research associate at the [[University of Dar es Salaam]], and has organised training, communication, extension, and teaching posts in India.

He served on the NGO Committee of the [[CGIAR]].<ref>[http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/pubs/books/2020conpro/apx02.pdf Appendix 2: Speakers—Biographical Notes] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120614073527/http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/pubs/pubs/books/2020conpro/apx02.pdf |date=14 June 2012 }}. Proceedings of the conference "2020 Vision: Sustainable Food Security for All by 2020. September 2001, Bonn, Germany". International Food Policy Research Institute, p. 231. Accessed 12 August 2011</ref>

